description:
**Amita Health Care Italia**, azienda leader nella distribuzione di materie prime per i settori Personal Care, Nutraceutico e Medical Device, è alla ricerca di una risorsa da inserire nel proprio laboratorio cosmetico.

**Descrizione della posizione**

La risorsa, riportando direttamente al Responsabile di Laboratorio, sarà coinvolta nelle attività di ricerca e sviluppo formulativo e fornirà supporto tecnico\-scientifico alle diverse funzioni aziendali.

In particolare, si occuperà di:

* Supportare le attività di sviluppo formulativo in ambito cosmetico;
* Collaborare con i Sales Manager durante visite tecniche presso i clienti;
* Ricercare, valutare e validare nuove materie prime;
* Fornire supporto tecnico\-scientifico alla divisione commerciale;
* Utilizzare la strumentazione di laboratorio di base per prove e test formulativi.

**Requisiti**

Cerchiamo candidati in possesso dei seguenti requisiti:

* Laurea triennale o magistrale in Farmacia, CTFA, Biotecnologie o discipline affini, oppure studenti in cerca di uno stage finalizzato alla tesi;
* Preferibile una breve esperienza in laboratori di Ricerca e Sviluppo cosmetico o in attività correlate alla produzione di prodotti finiti;
* Buona/ottima conoscenza della lingua inglese (livello B2/C1\);
* Buona conoscenza del pacchetto Microsoft Office;
* Attitudine al lavoro in team, precisione e capacità organizzative;
* Dinamicità, proattività e orientamento al risultato;
* Capacità di problem solving e gestione delle priorità;
* Disponibilità a effettuare trasferte occasionali.

**Cosa offriamo**

* Stage retribuito con rimborso spese di € 600,00 al mese;
* Percorso formativo in un contesto dinamico e innovativo;
* Possibilità di acquisire competenze tecniche nel settore cosmetico e delle materie prime.

**Sede di lavoro**

Lainate (MI), raggiungibile esclusivamente con mezzo proprio.

**Orario di lavoro**

Full\-time, dal lunedì al venerdì.

**Pari opportunità e privacy**

La ricerca è rivolta a candidati di entrambi i sessi, ai sensi delle Leggi 903/77 e 125/91\.

I dati personali saranno trattati nel rispetto del Regolamento UE 2016/679 (GDPR) e della normativa vigente in materia di protezione dei dati personali.

Retribuzione: €600,00 al mese

Sede di lavoro: Di persona

SYNLAB è una multinazionale, presente in Europa, Asia, Africa e Sud America, composta da quasi 30 mila dipendenti, che collaborano con il principale obiettivo di migliorare il benessere dei pazienti.


In Italia, con un team di oltre 4 mila professionisti, **SYNLAB rappresenta il più importante e vasto gruppo di diagnostica integrata nei Medical Center e il più importante interlocutore dei servizi di Laboratorio**. Lombardia, Veneto, Friuli\-Venezia Giulia, Toscana, Emilia\-Romagna, Liguria, Lazio e Campania sono le regioni in cui si sviluppa principalmente l'attività di SYNLAB che è comunque presente in tutta Italia con partner accreditati.



La Mission: **fornire informazioni diagnostiche utili per una vita sana e per il benessere di tutti**.


La Vision: **una leadership conquistata attraverso l’eccellenza del servizio a favore delle persone e della comunità medica, con una diagnostica di altissima qualità**.


I Valori: **passione, responsabilità e customer centricity.**



Scopri di più: https://www.synlab.it





**Posizione:**
--------------

For the Operations team of SYNLAB Italia, we are looking for a **Lean Manager** who will be responsible for leading continuous improvement initiatives and contributing to processes transformation across Italy.


The position does not include direct people management, and requires a strong cross\-functional leadership on projects and a constant interaction with diverse stakeholders, like country and corporate functions, as well as international counterparts.


We are looking for a pragmatic, energetic, and assertive person—not a back\-office or purely analytical profile, but a true change agent who can work directly on processes, engage people, and deliver tangible improvements in efficiency, performance, and ways of working.

**Contract and package**


Permanent contract



CCNL Commercio – Level 1



Indicative gross annual salary range: €43,000 – €47,000 \+ MBO

**Main responsibilities**


The person will be responsible for:

* Leading Lean projects and continuous improvement initiatives, leveraging the STS (SYNLAB Transformation System) methodology;
* Analysing operational processes, identifying inefficiencies, waste, bottlenecks and improvement opportunities;
* Defining and monitoring action plans, KPIs, milestones and targeted results;
* Facilitating workshops, problem\-solving activities, Kaizen events and on\-site discussions;
* Supporting process standardisation and the deployment of Lean/STS best practices;
* Supporting change, influencing stakeholders and operational teams even without direct hierarchical authority;
* Collaborating with the Group headquarters and with the Group STS community.

**Requisiti:**
--------------

The ideal candidate has:

* At least 7 years of experience in Lean, Operational Excellence, Continuous Improvement, Industrial Engineering or Process Improvement roles;
* Previous experience in structured industrial, manufacturing or production environments;
* Hands\-on experience in change management projects with measurable impact on processes, KPIs and people;
* Solid knowledge of Lean tools, including VSM, A3, PDCA, Kaizen, 5S, Standard Work, Visual Management and Root Cause Analysis;
* Excellent command of Excel and PowerPoint;
* Good knowledge of Microsoft SharePoint, Planner and Visio will be considered a plus;
* Excellent written and spoken English;
* Availability to travel across Italy, approximately 30% of the time.


Previous experience in regulated or complex industrial sectors, such as pharma, medical devices, chemical, food, packaging or automotive, will be considered a plus.

**Soft skills**


The ideal candidate also brings:

* Strong drive and result orientation;
* Assertiveness and influencing skills;
* Energy, ambition and pragmatism;
* Hands\-on approach;
* Problem\-solving attitude and change management skills;
* Ability to engage people and constructively challenge the status quo.

**Altre informazioni:**
-----------------------

**What we offer**


The opportunity to join an international and evolving environment, with a role highly exposed to Operations processes and Lean/STS transformation initiatives within SYNLAB Italia.

*The job offer is open to candidates of all genders, in compliance with Legislative Decree no. 198/2006, as amended and supplemented, and Legislative Decrees nos. 215 and 216/2003 on equal treatment.*

*Applicants are invited to read the privacy notice pursuant to Articles 13 and 14 of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 at the following address:* *https://www.synlab.it/privacy\-policy*

Job Summary :

Our clinical activities are growing rapidly, and we are currently seeking a full\-time Clinical Research Associate (law 68/99 Art. 18\) to join our Clinical Monitoring team in Italy. This position will work with a team to accomplish tasks and projects that are instrumental to the company’s success. If you want an exciting career where you use your previous expertise and can develop and grow your career even further, then this is the opportunity for you.  

Medpace will provide comprehensive initial and ongoing training depending on your previous experience.
Responsibilities :
* Conduct qualification, initiation, monitoring, and closeout visits at research sites in compliance with the approved protocol;
* Communication with the medical site staff including coordinators, clinical research physicians, and their site staff;
* Verify adequate investigator qualifications, training and resources, including facilities, laboratories, equipment, and staff;
* Medical record and research source documentation verification against case report form data, including informing the site staff of any entry errors, ensuring good documentation practices are being adhered to and communicating protocol deviations appropriately per SOPs, GCP, and applicable regulatory requirements;
* Verification that the investigator is enrolling only eligible subjects;
* Regulatory document review;
* Medical device and/or investigational product/drug accountability and inventory;
* Verification and review of adverse events, serious adverse events, concomitant medications and corresponding illnesses to confirm accurate data reporting in accordance with the protocol;
* Assess the clinical research site’s patient recruitment and retention success and offering suggestions for improvement; and
* Completion of monitoring reports and follow\-up letters, which includes providing summaries of the significant findings, deviations, deficiencies, and recommended actions to secure compliance.


Qualifications :
* Master degree in health\-related field;
* Willing to travel 60\-80% nationally;
* Familiarity with Microsoft® Office;
* CRA certification completed as per DMC 15 /11 / 2011;
* Previous experience as CRA;
* Fluent in English and Italian language;
* Strong communication and presentation skills a plus.


Medpace Overview :

Medpace is a full\-service clinical contract research organization (CRO). We provide Phase I\-IV clinical development services to the biotechnology, pharmaceutical and medical device industries. Our mission is to accelerate the global development of safe and effective medical therapeutics through its scientific and disciplined approach. We leverage local regulatory and therapeutic expertise across all major areas including oncology, cardiology, metabolic disease, endocrinology, central nervous system, anti\-viral and anti\-infective. Headquartered in Cincinnati, Ohio, employing more than 6,000 people across 40\+ countries.
Why Medpace? :

People. Purpose. Passion. Make a Difference Tomorrow. Join Us Today.  

The work we’ve done over the past 30\+ years has positively impacted the lives of countless patients and families who face hundreds of diseases across all key therapeutic areas. The work we do today will improve the lives of people living with illness and disease in the future. **Medpace Perks**

* Flexible work environment
* Competitive compensation and benefits package
* Competitive PTO packages
* Structured career paths with opportunities for professional growth
* Company\-sponsored employee appreciation events
* Employee health and wellness initiatives

**Awards*** Recognized by Forbes as one of America's Most Successful Midsize Companies in 2021, 2022, 2023 and 2024
* Continually recognized with CRO Leadership Awards from Life Science Leader magazine based on expertise, quality, capabilities, reliability, and compatibility

 **What to Expect Next**
A Medpace team member will review your qualifications and, if interested, you will be contacted with details for next steps.
